Understand the dataset and Data cleaningÂ¶

  • The dataset consists of 15 columns (6 columns with continuous data and 9 columns with discrete data).
  • There are 2399 records (7.37% of the dataset) containing invalid data like ?.
  • These records will be removed from the dataset since they formed only a small proportion of the dataset.
  • The number of records remaining is 30162.

# drop invalid records

df_train_cleaned = df_train[df_train['workclass'] != '?']
df_train_cleaned = df_train_cleaned[df_train_cleaned['occupation'] != '?']
df_train_cleaned = df_train_cleaned[df_train_cleaned['native-country'] != '?']

print("Total number of records after dropping:", len(df_train_cleaned))
print("Total number of records dropped:", len(df_train) - len(df_train_cleaned))

education-numÂ¶

Hyper Parameter Tuning & Cross ValidationÂ¶

InÂ [94]:
start_time = datetime.now()

parameters = {'n_estimators':[25, 50], 
              'max_depth':np.arange(1,10), 
              'min_samples_leaf':np.arange(1,10)}

model_RF = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=123)
gsc = GridSearchCV(estimator=model_RF, param_grid=parameters, cv=5, scoring='roc_auc')
grid_result = gsc.fit(x_train, y_train)
best_params_RF = grid_result.best_params_
AUC_RF = max(gsc.cv_results_['mean_test_score'])        # AUC of the best parameter, cross-validated 5 times

print('AUC of Random Forest Train:', AUC_RF)
print('Best Parameters:', best_params_RF)

end_time = datetime.now()
print('Time taken for hyper parameter tuning: {}'.format(end_time - start_time))

AUC of Random Forest Train: 0.9119819527211476
